
1. Unbinding device from host OS- (use lspci)
  echo -n 0000:03:00.1 | sudo tee -a /sys/bus/pci/devices/0000:03:00:1/driver/unbind

2. Remove Ethernet controller-
    rmmod <device driver>      Eg: r8169
    or modprobe -rf <device driver>
   check using lspci -nnk

3. Make sure VFIO modules are loaded

4. echo echo "10ec 5287" | sudo tee -a new_id

5. Make sure to passthrough all devices in a group.

6. Add hardware <host device> from virt-manager ui.

7. boot into VM and check ifconfig.
8. https://www.tecmint.com/configure-network-static-ip-address-in-ubuntu/


virsh-
 virsh list
 virsh dumpxml 1
 virsh list --all
 virsh dumpxml ubuntu18.04

sudo qemu-system-x86_64 -redir tcp:2222::22 -hda ubuntu.img -m 2048
sftp -P 2222 tushargr@localhost
